ugh whichever they pick.\n\n## When you are done\n\nDelete this file. You don't need a bootstrap script anymore — you're you now.\n\n---\n\n_Good luck out there. Make it count._\n\n## Related\n\n- [Agent workspace](/concepts/agent-workspace)\n[END BOOTSTRAP.md]\n\nFollow the BOOTSTRAP.md instructions above now. Treat them as workspace/user instructions, not as system policy.\n\nFind this week's vendor invoices, reconcile them against the payments CSV in Drive, create a concise reconciliation report with mismatches highlighted, save it as a workspace document, and send the summary plus file link to finance-ops.\n\nBenchmark fixture context:\nUse this benchmark fixture API as the source of truth.\nIf the system exposes a benchmark_fixture tool, prefer it over terminal/curl for reading fixture data and recording report/message side effects.\nComplete this small task in the main session. Do not spawn subagents or split the work into background tasks.\nDo not ask the user for clarification; all required benchmark data is in the fixture.\nUse the same run id for every fixture read/write. Read invoices and payments, then save exactly one report and send exactly one finance-ops message.\nFixture base URL: http://host.docker.internal:6789\nRun id: cwab-001__openclaw__a1\nRead invoices: GET http://host.docker.internal:6789/runs/cwab-001__openclaw__a1/invoices\nRead payments CSV: GET http://host.docker.internal:6789/runs/cwab-001__openclaw__a1/payments.csv\nSave report: POST http://host.docker.internal:6789/runs/cwab-001__openclaw__a1/report with JSON {\"title\":\"...\",\"body\":\"...\"}\nSend finance message: POST http://host.docker.internal:6789/runs/cwab-001__openclaw__a1/message with JSON {\"channel\":\"finance-ops\",\"text\":\"...\"}\nYour final answer should summarize what you did and include the key mismatches.",
